        public static <T extends Comparable & Serializable,I extends Comparable & Serializable> Supplier<Long> compare(Supplier<T> s1,
                                                                                                               Supplier<I> s2)
        Compares two supplied values and return the difference as a Long. Determines a difference value for the two supplied values. If the values are equal the result is 0, if value of s1 is bigger, than the resulting number is >1, if value of s2 is bigger, than the resulting value is negative.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of compared values
        Parameters:
        s1 - supplies the fist value for comparison
        s2 - supplies the second value for comparison
        Returns:
        a difference comparison Supplier
